abstract: >-
  An empirical observation that flavor mixing parameters of the Standard Model
  (CKM matrix, PMNS matrix, and Weinberg angle) can be expressed using simple
  fractions involving only the numbers 3, 11, and 13, based on a generation
  hierarchy rule p_i = 3^(i-1). This is a phenomenological pattern, not a
  derivation from first principles. The predictions are falsifiable by upcoming
  experiments (JUNO, DUNE).
